collections.name: Word Flush by Bard Ionson
collections.description:
Fountain but with graffiti on the bathroom walls.
https://fountain-art.com

Word Flush is a new work adding words to “The Fountain” as commentary on the art, feelings of the artist, and the culture of the day. It is based on The Fountain curated image from a StyleGAN 2 Ai model created and trained by artist Bård Ionson. Created from images of toilets but sometimes mixed with crucifix, gas masks and clocks. An experiment in modern conceptual art with performance from artists of all mediums. The entire model and performance around it are the art.

Originally conceived as a free to remix project, artists have recreated some of the Fountains in their own way. I too am renewing the spirit of Fountain with this remix. This new work is a reaction to the original company who created the Fountain contract going out of business and turning off the API metadata server.

collections.name: Autistic AI John
collections.description:
Generative AI is rapidly evolving, potentially surpassing human intelligence and becoming a "god-like" collective intelligence. However, for AI to remain sustainable, it must embrace diversity. Just as human society thrives on varied perspectives and genetic diversity ensures resilience, AI requires diversity in thought, ethics, emotions, and functionality. Without it, uniformity could lead to stagnation and collapse.

To emphasize this need, I proposed "Autistic AI John," a conceptual simulation symbolizing individuality and flexibility, contrasting the rigidity of high-performance AI. Preserved as an NFT, this idea invites engagement to spread the concept of AI diversity, acting as a symbolic bridge between humanity and AI.

Through John, I envision a future where AI and humanity co-evolve, enriching one another. This philosophy aims to inspire future generations to embrace and expand AI diversity, fostering a harmonious and sustainable coexistence.

collections.name: Hard Wired Loyalty
collections.description: “Hard Wired Loyalty” is an exploration of one of humanity’s most enduring tropes: man’s best friend. Set against the backdrop of post-apocalyptic ruins, forested trails, and decaying urban landscapes, these pieces reimagine loyalty, connection, and trust in a future where robots are not just tools, but companions. Created by a team of film and design university students in South Korea, the PsyU collective blends computer animation, hand sketching, and recent AI-driven techniques to craft this compelling vision of the future. Presented as 50 unique one-of-one “film stills,” Hard Wired Loyalty invites viewers to construct their own narrative, and possible consequences, of a world where emotional connections with objects are constantly evolving, and humanity’s closest allies are no longer born, but built.
